# CODEOWNERS — regulated-path ownership for NEUROGAN-ERP
#
# Per AGENTS.md §6.3, this file declares the owner of paths that the FDA/483
# response treats as regulated. PRs touching any of these paths auto-request
# review from the owner.
#
# In the current solo-dev staffing model (project memory), branch protection
# is intentionally configured with require_code_owner_reviews: false — GitHub
# does not let an author approve their own PR, so requiring owner review would
# block self-merge. CODEOWNERS still surfaces review-worthy changes by
# auto-CCing the owner on the PR; it is *not* a merge gate today.
#
# When a second developer joins, flip require_code_owner_reviews to true on
# branch protection and this file becomes an enforced control.

# Default owner — catch-all so every PR has someone CCed.
*                          @fhneurogan

# Regulated paths — called out explicitly so the intent is visible in the repo,
# even though the * rule above would match them anyway.

# Schema: tables, columns, enums, drizzle-zod insert/select shapes.
/shared/schema.ts          @fhneurogan

# Storage layer: business rules, state transitions, audit-wrapped writes.
/server/db-storage.ts      @fhneurogan
/server/storage.ts         @fhneurogan
/server/storage/**         @fhneurogan

# Auth, sessions, password policy, signature ceremony (lands in F-02 / F-04).
/server/auth/**            @fhneurogan

# Audit trail infrastructure (lands in F-03).
/server/audit/**           @fhneurogan

# Regulated state machines (lands in F-05).
/server/state/**           @fhneurogan

# Migration SQL — every migration is hand-reviewed per AGENTS.md §5.2.
/migrations/**             @fhneurogan
/drizzle.config.ts         @fhneurogan

# The working-rules document itself.
/AGENTS.md                 @fhneurogan
/FDA/AGENTS.md             @fhneurogan

# CI + CODEOWNERS meta.
/.github/workflows/**      @fhneurogan
/.github/CODEOWNERS        @fhneurogan
